suffer the worst of the
conflict, caught in

37:39.591 --> 37:44.996 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the crossfire of FARC guerrillas
fighting
the army and paramilitaries, the
river and

37:45.029 --> 37:49.334 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
its banks converted into a large
cemetery.

37:49.367 --> 37:52.871 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Maxima Asprilla is one of the
women who sang
in Cartagena.

37:52.904 --> 37:56.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAXIMA ASPRILLA, Colombia
(through translator):
When I was singing -- and that's
why we sang

37:56.975 --> 38:00.979 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with such emotion and effort --
the only thing
I was thinking was, we want
peace.

38:01.012 --> 38:07.152 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Perhaps because of
being so hard-hit
by the conflict, Bojaya
residents voted overwhelmingly,

38:07.185 --> 38:10.955 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
95 percent, in support of the
peace accords.

38:10.989 --> 38:16.661 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Now, with the peace deal
rejected nationally
and mired in uncertainty, many
here fear they

38:16.694 --> 38:21.299 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
may have lost their only and
long-awaited
chance to live in peace.

38:21.332 --> 38:26.037 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MACARIA ALLIN (through
translator): We feel
abandoned, betrayed.

38:26.070 --> 38:29.107 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We thought they would support
us, those who
have lived the war.

38:29.140 --> 38:32.610 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The half-country who voted for
no turned their
back on us.

38:32.644 --> 38:38.183 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: The peace process,
throughout
its four years of negotiations,
has generated

38:38.216 --> 38:40.351 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
fierce political debate.

38:40.385 --> 38:46.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the criticism by vocal
opponents prompted
President Juan Manuel Santos to
call the referendum,

38:47.025 --> 38:50.495 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with the hope that a show of
public support
could strengthen the deal.

38:50.528 --> 38:56.734 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUAN MANUEL SANTOS, Colombian
President: Many
people warned me against it, but
I said this

38:56.768 --> 39:03.942 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is something that I believe will
be positive
for the whole process.

39:03.975 --> 39:07.879 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The decision backfired because
we lost by
a very small margin.

39:07.912 --> 39:13.718 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: With only 37
percent of voters
bothering to go to the polls,
and the no side

39:13.751 --> 39:21.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
winning by a mere 53,000 votes
out of 13.5
million, there is perhaps no one
more consumed

39:21.092 --> 39:26.664 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with why the deal was rejected
than the man
who just won the Nobel Peace
Prize for its

39:26.698 --> 39:28.032 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
signing.

39:28.066 --> 39:32.470 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Why do you think that Colombians
voted against
the peace accords?

39:32.503 --> 39:38.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUAN MANUEL SANTOS: Of course,
there's been
a lot of misinformation, a lot
of lack of

39:39.010 --> 39:40.945 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
information.

39:40.979 --> 39:49.420 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And maybe I'm a bit responsible
for not being
more effective in this process
of telling

39:49.454 --> 39:52.457 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
people what the agreement was
all about.

39:52.490 --> 39:57.629 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: The peace accords
were defeated
by a no campaign led by Santos
archrival and

39:57.662 --> 40:01.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
former President Alvaro Uribe
and his Central
Democratic Party.

40:01.699 --> 40:07.038 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the campaign has been
questioned over
the claims it made to voters:
that the country

40:07.071 --> 40:11.976 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
would become a socialist state
like Venezuela,
or that FARC leaders would
receive impunity

40:12.010 --> 40:13.845 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for their crimes.

40:13.878 --> 40:19.450 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Rodrigo Uprimny, a
constitutional law expert
close to the peace talks, says
the no campaign

40:19.484 --> 40:22.620 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
even made claims that had
nothing to do with
the peace accord.

40:22.654 --> 40:25.056 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RODRIGO UPRIMNY, Constitutional
Law Expert:
They say to them, these peace
accords are

40:25.089 --> 40:32.230 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
going to destroy your family
because this
peace accord is in favor of
homosexuality,

40:32.263 --> 40:34.332 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
which quite clearly is not true.

40:34.365 --> 40:40.705 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Ivan Zuluaga, the
Central Democratic
Party's director and a former
presidential

40:40.738 --> 40:46.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
candidate who lost to Santos in
the last election,
says the no vote's victory sends
a clear mandate

40:46.911 --> 40:48.680 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to overhaul the agreements.

40:48.713 --> 40:51.549 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
IVAN ZULUAGA, Director, Central
Democratic
Party: They have to recognize
that Colombians

40:51.582 --> 40:58.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
vote for it, so they have to
accept not only
the government, but even the
FARC deep changes,

40:59.023 --> 41:00.825 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
fundamental changes.

41:00.858 --> 41:04.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: FARC leaders have
said they are
open to making some changes, but
warn it will

41:04.729 --> 41:07.865 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
be difficult change the
agreement's core.

41:07.899 --> 41:12.270 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We traveled via river from
Bojaya to visit
a FARC unit.

41:12.303 --> 41:17.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mid-level commanders known as
Pablo Atrato
and Natalie Mistral, a French
citizen, led

41:17.809 --> 41:23.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
us to a camp where their troops,
like thousands
of others spread out amongst
jungle enclaves,

41:23.314 --> 41:26.184 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
are waiting amid the
uncertainty.

41:26.217 --> 41:29.287 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Both Mistral and Atrato were at
negotiations
in Havana.

41:29.320 --> 41:32.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PABLO ATRATO, FARC (through
translator): After
years of negotiations, to
resolve all this

41:32.657 --> 41:34.959 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in two or three months, I don't
think it's
possible.

41:34.992 --> 41:38.930 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: The peace accords
will grant
immunity to much of the FARC's
rank-and-file,

41:38.963 --> 41:44.769 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
but those accused of crimes
against humanity
will receive alternative
sentences in exchange

41:44.802 --> 41:49.374 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for confessing the truth, not
jail, but restrictions
on their liberty.

41:49.407 --> 41:51.843 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But many in the opposition say
that is unacceptable.

41:51.876 --> 41:55.179 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
IVAN ZULUAGA: They have to go to
jail five
years.

41:55.213 --> 42:00.318 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If they are in jail, they are
not able to
be eligible politically.

42:00.351 --> 42:05.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, instead of that, the
treatment says,
and the agreement with the FARC
says, that

42:06.023 --> 42:13.731 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they aren't going to jail and
they can be
eligible for any major president
or congress,

42:13.765 --> 42:14.832 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for example.

42:14.866 --> 42:16.534 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RODRIGO UPRIMNY: But that's --
that's the
deal.

42:16.567 --> 42:22.673 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If you want an armed political
-- an armed
political actor like the FARC to
become a

42:22.707 --> 42:27.545 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
peaceful political actor, then
you can not
block them to make politics.

42:27.578 --> 42:30.348 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's the crucial issue in a
peace accord.

42:30.381 --> 42:35.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NATALIE MISTRAL, FARC (through
translator):
I'm not willing to spend time in
jail, and

42:35.920 --> 42:38.523 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm not willing to let my
superiors go to
jail either.

42:38.556 --> 42:41.726 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
To serve jail time would nullify
us politically.

42:41.759 --> 42:44.028 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's unacceptable within a peace
negotiation.

42:44.061 --> 42:49.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: While Santos has
said his government
is trying to satisfy the no
side, he has made

42:49.434 --> 42:53.137 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
clear there will be disagreement
on issues
in reaching a new agreement.

42:53.171 --> 42:59.043 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Santos' government and the
FARC face an
enormous challenge: making
sufficient changes

42:59.076 --> 43:04.449 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to the peace agreement to gain
broader support
of the public, without making
the tectonic-shifting

43:04.482 --> 43:07.018 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
changes that could break it
down.

43:07.051 --> 43:13.858 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PABLO ATRATO (through
translator): The risks
are that this gets drawn out and
we end up

43:13.891 --> 43:15.893 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
again in a spiral of war.

43:15.927 --> 43:19.497 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that's how it could end
up, if we're
not capable in the next two or
three months

43:19.530 --> 43:21.332 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to find a way out of this.

43:21.365 --> 43:26.571 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUAN MANUEL SANTOS: I am
absolutely determined
not to allow the country to go
back to war

43:26.604 --> 43:27.672 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with FARC.

43:27.705 --> 43:29.173 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The FARC doesn't want it.

43:29.207 --> 43:30.975 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We don't want it.

43:31.008 --> 43:42.787 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we're trying to find the
best and the
most rapid path to get out of
this situation,

43:42.820 --> 43:45.556 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
and that's to have a new
agreement as soon
as possible.

43:45.590 --> 43:49.961 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Santos told us he
hopes to get
a new peace deal by the end of
the year.

43:49.994 --> 43:52.597 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But delay could jeopardize the
current cease-fire.

43:52.630 --> 43:58.836 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Bojaya residents like Maxima
Asprilla are
finally feeling peace in their
town, and have

43:58.870 --> 44:00.872 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
seen changes among the FARC.

44:00.905 --> 44:05.843 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MAXIMA ASPRILLA (through
translator): After
having signed the cease-fire,
they got into

44:05.877 --> 44:08.446 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a different mode and the tension
went down.

44:08.479 --> 44:13.484 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NADJA DROST: In fact, the FARC
even apologized
to the community last year.

44:13.518 --> 44:16.053 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator): We ask
you to forgive
us.

44:16.087 --> 44:21.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: After so many years
of singing
lamentations for their dead,
these women hope

44:21.125 --> 44:27.865 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to have a reason to compose a
song in celebration
of life, and the peace they so
badly want.

44:27.899 --> 44:40.611 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"We Colombians," they sing, "ask
that war
not repeat."

44:40.645 --> 44:45.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But whether Bojaya's plea for
peace is answered
is far from certain.

44:45.182 --> 44:51.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
From Bojaya, Colombia, reporting
with Bruno
Federico, I'm Nadja Drost for
the "PBS NewsHour."

44:51.122 --> 44:55.560 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And you can see
more of Nadja's
interview with the Colombian
president on

44:55.593 --> 45:07.605 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
our Web site, PBS.org/NewsHour.

45:07.638 --> 45:13.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now a special treat on this
Halloween, a story
about the magic of movies and
zombies.

45:13.778 --> 45:16.647 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The "NewsHour"'s Mike Melia has
our update.

45:16.681 --> 45:21.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIKE MELIA: You don't often get
to see someone's
dreams come true, even if they
are the stuff

45:22.019 --> 45:25.222 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of nightmares.

45:25.256 --> 45:29.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We first met Sam Suchmann and
Mattie Zufelt
two years ago, when all they had
was a big

45:29.460 --> 45:32.530 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
idea and a Kickstarter to make
an epic zombie
movie.

45:32.563 --> 45:36.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MATTIE ZUFELT, Filmmaker: It's
going to be
like between horror and comedy,
drama, same

45:36.634 --> 45:38.402 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
kind of thing.

45:38.436 --> 45:46.010 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SAM SUCHMANN, Filmmaker: We have
every average,
everyday teen drama, like love
triangles,

45:46.043 --> 45:50.214 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
or like heartbreaks or betrayals
or people
living like...

45:50.247 --> 45:52.116 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATTIE ZUFELT: Or it could be
like teenagers'
secret life.

45:52.149 --> 45:54.785 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SAM SUCHMANN: What I do to
Mattie is, I leave
him behind.

45:54.819 --> 45:55.786 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MATTIE ZUFELT: Yes.

45:55.820 --> 45:57.254 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SAM SUCHMANN: And that is not
cool.

45:57.288 --> 45:58.255 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
So...

45:58.289 --> 45:59.256 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MATTIE ZUFELT: No.

45:59.290 --> 46:01.025 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You can't leave a friend behind.

46:01.058 --> 46:03.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIKE MELIA: The best friends --
both have
Down syndrome -- first met at
the Special

46:03.728 --> 46:05.496 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Olympics in grade school.

46:05.529 --> 46:08.699 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
From his living room in Rhode
Island, Sam
told us a very personal reason
for wanting

46:08.733 --> 46:10.468 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to make the movie.

46:10.501 --> 46:14.972 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SAM SUCHMANN: My whole life, I
feel like I
never fit in anywhere or had a
voice, but

46:15.006 --> 46:17.241 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
someday, that will change.

46:17.274 --> 46:19.076 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I will be somebody.

46:19.110 --> 46:20.645 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And that day is today.

46:20.678 --> 46:23.247 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MIKE MELIA: In many ways, Sam
was right.

46:23.280 --> 46:26.283 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Their lives were about to change
in dramatic
ways.

46:26.317 --> 46:28.452 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Their Kickstarter raised nearly
$70,000.

46:28.486 --> 46:34.558 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They gathered together family,
friends, along
with film industry and special
effects professionals.

46:34.592 --> 46:36.994 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It was all happening.

46:37.028 --> 46:41.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We got invited on set for a day,
when they
were filming a party scene on a
yacht.

46:41.332 --> 46:44.635 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Sam and Mattie originally wanted
a cruise
ship, but this was close.

46:44.669 --> 46:48.406 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Peter Farrelly, behind hits like
"Dumb and
Dumber" and "Something About
Mary," was also

46:48.439 --> 46:49.674 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
on set.

46:49.707 --> 46:52.476 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I was transformed into a zombie
-- but more
on that later.

46:52.510 --> 46:54.779 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The day before, "The Jersey
Shore"'s D.J.

46:54.812 --> 46:56.313 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Pauly D. was there.

46:56.347 --> 47:00.217 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He had been at the top of Sam
and Mattie's
wish list for celebrity cameos.

47:00.251 --> 47:02.186 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In some ways, they were becoming
famous.

47:02.219 --> 47:05.890 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATTIE ZUFELT: I want to be
famous because
I want to be a deejay.

47:05.923 --> 47:06.891 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SAM SUCHMANN: Yes.

47:06.924 --> 47:11.762 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I want to be famous because I
love to sing.

47:11.796 --> 47:13.764 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MATTIE ZUFELT: Yes.

47:13.798 --> 47:17.101 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He has a good voice.

47:17.134 --> 47:20.438 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SAM SUCHMANN: I'm a singer.

47:20.471 --> 47:21.572 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And I can rap, too.

47:21.605 --> 47:23.007 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm do a little rap.

47:23.040 --> 47:24.575 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Maybe you want to hear.

47:24.608 --> 47:27.578 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MIKE MELIA: I would love to hear
it.

47:27.611 --> 47:28.579 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yes.

47:28.612 --> 47:29.580 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SAM SUCHMANN: Right here.

47:29.613 --> 47:30.581 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(RAPPING)

47:30.614 --> 47:32.049 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MATTIE ZUFELT: Yes, that's
really good.

47:32.083 --> 47:33.851 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
You're good.

47:33.884 --> 47:37.688 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIKE MELIA: There are no record
deals yet,
but since our story first aired,
Sam and Mattie

47:37.722 --> 47:42.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have been profiled by "People"
magazine, "The
Today Show," The Huffington
Post, just to

47:42.059 --> 47:45.663 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
