50:54.785 --> 50:59.423 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GERRY CARTER, Smithsonian
Researcher: I'm
Gerry Carter, and I study
food-sharing relationships

50:59.456 --> 51:01.091 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in vampire bats.

51:01.125 --> 51:04.094 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Vampire bats are small,
neotropical bats.

51:04.128 --> 51:08.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They weigh about 30 grams, and
they drink
nothing but blood.

51:08.799 --> 51:13.904 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The legend of the vampire
actually came first
before the bat was discovered by
Europeans.

51:13.938 --> 51:17.775 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, the bat is actually named
after the monster,
and not the other way around.

51:17.808 --> 51:22.746 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One idea about vampire bats
that's very common,
especially in Latin America, is
that most

51:22.780 --> 51:23.747 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
bats are vampire bats.

51:23.781 --> 51:25.582 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And that's certainly not true.

51:25.616 --> 51:32.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are only three species of
vampire bats,
and there are roughly 1,300
species of bats.

51:32.389 --> 51:36.393 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The common vampire bat usually
feeds on mammals
and livestock.

51:36.427 --> 51:40.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The white-winged vampire bat
will often climb
along the underside of a branch
to feed on

51:40.831 --> 51:42.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the toes of a bird.

51:42.666 --> 51:47.071 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the hairy-legged vampire bat
will actually
land on a bird like a chicken
and hide in

51:47.104 --> 51:48.072 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the feathers.

51:48.105 --> 51:49.873 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, it's like a giant tick.

51:49.907 --> 51:54.545 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Vampire bats have these
razor-sharp teeth
that they use to make a small
cut, and then

51:54.578 --> 51:56.413 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
